SELECT
    c.customer_name,
    SUM(s.sales) AS total_sales,
    SUM(s.profit) AS total_profit
FROM sales s
JOIN customer c
ON s.customer_id = c.customer_id
GROUP BY c.customer_name
ORDER BY total_sales DESC;

Query Explanation: Customer-wise Sales and Profit Analysis
This query is used to analyze total sales and total profit generated by each customer.
What the query does:
-Combines sales data with customer details
-Aggregates transaction-level data to the customer level
-Ranks customers based on profit contribution
-Identifies high-value customers
-Supports customer segmentation
